keyValuePair.Value: Why are you sticking with %1s?
People are wondering why %1s is still getting picked for the starting XI when he's obviously struggling so badly for form. Are you expecting to see signs of improvement soon?
He's on borrowed time at the moment.
I respect the lad and rate him as a player. But we can only be patient for so long. I think he knows that the time's coming when I'll have to start leaving him out of the team.
He'll play through it.
Every player has ups and downs during a career. I believe in %1s and value what he brings to the team. I think he'll play his way through this bad patch and be back on form soon.
He needs to play games to get his form back.
As manager, I have to balance things. If I leave %1s out, he'll just be stuck in a rut. I think he needs to play games and, eventually, things will start to click again for him and for the team.
Did %1s look his old self today?
It's been difficult for %1s recently and you've had to try everything to try and get him back to his best. Do you think we saw him come through the other side of his bad spell in today's game?
He's a tough lad.
I think you've got to recognise the lad's resilience. He knows he's been struggling, in and out of the team. But he's kept his head down, worked hard, and today he got his reward.
He needs to get on a good run.
It's not going to happen overnight but today was a good start. It's been a difficult time for him. Now he needs a run of games playing like that to convince us all he's back to his best.
Let's hope he's on a roll now.
I was really pleased for %1s today. He's an important player for us and that's the kind of performance we expect from him. If he can get on a good run now, the team will definitely win games.
Will %1s get his chance?
%1s's good form has been a real plus for your boys recently and I'm sure you must be thinking about giving him more playing time. What are your plans for today? Will we see him from the start?
I have to rotate the squad.
It's a long season and I need to keep everybody on their toes. All the players want to start games, of course. %1s is no different. He just has to make the most of every chance he gets to play.
I have to adapt for each game.

It's important to have a plan to deal with each opponent we face. Every game's different and we have to adapt the players and tactics we use. I'll always pick the team I think can get the right result.
I've got no problem with the lad.
I need to pick the team I think is best set up to win the game. It's nothing personal and I hope the lad knows that. I'm just doing what I need to do to keep the club moving forward.
Were you happy with %1s's display?
The draw was a disappointment but you must have seen %1s's performance as a positive. He definitely looks to be getting back to his best. Are you expecting him to improve over the next few games?
The lad deserves some respect.
It's not been easy for the lad recently. There's real competition for places here, but he's kept his head down and worked hard to get a bit of form back. You have to praise his resilience, I think.
He can kick on from here.
Of course I'm happy for the lad. He looked like he was enjoying his football again today. Let's hope he's over his bad patch and we see a run of performances like that from him now.
There were good signs, for sure.
Everyone knows how important %1s is to us. Yes, he looked more comfortable today, but we need to have him back at his absolute best if we're going to be competitive this season.
Was %1s's performance a plus today?
You probably feel frustrated to have lost the game, but %1s looked like he was getting back to his best out there. How important could that be to the team moving forward now?
He's a real fighter.

I think you've got to admire the lad's resilience. He's been struggling for form and the team didn't have a good day today. But he battled through and I'm sure that he can inspire a decent run from us now.
He can build on this display.
The lad's attitude has been first class. He knows he's been struggling but he's kept going and today showed good signs. I hope we'll see a run of better performances from him now.
He can give us more.
We need %1s at his absolute best. He showed good signs today that he might be over his bad patch, but we'll need even more from him to make a difference in games like today's.
Will you remain patient with %1s?
A good result for the team today, but you must still be worried about %1s's form. You gave him the start but he seemed to struggle again. How long can you afford to remain patient with him?
Maybe he needs a bit of time out of the team.
Well, nobody can say we haven't given %1s chances to get his form back. Today we won and got away with it. But I can't take more risks. I've got other players ready to take his place now.
I'll always back the boy.
This is a confidence issue. I know the difference %1s can make to this team. I won't put extra pressure on him by dropping him. I want to do everything I can to help him through this poor spell.
He can't take anything for granted.
I rate %1s and want him back to his best. But he knows he's like any other player in the squad. If he's struggling, he'll be dropped and will then have to fight his way back into the team.
Is %1s going to struggle for a starting place?
%1s missed games through suspension and has been struggling for form. It seems pretty obvious that he's going to find it difficult to win a place in your starting line-up. Would you agree?
He knows what the situation is.
I'm sure %1s realises we've given him every chance recently. But there comes a point where the team is the priority. I have to give other players an opportunity to stake a claim now.
I treat every player the same.

I try to keep things clear and simple. It's the same for every player here, including %1s. If you get a chance to play, you have to take it. Prove to me you're worth a place in the XI for the following game.
We'll just look forward.

There's no point in dwelling on past mistakes. I definitely won't hold anything against him. He's been struggling lately, but I expect to see him bounce back. He's still an important player for this team.

There's no point in dwelling on past mistakes. I definitely won't hold anything against him. He's been struggling lately, but I expect to see him bounce back. He's still an important player for this team.

%1s has been struggling for form lately. You brought him off early today. What was the thinking behind that? Were you trying to send the lad a message about his place in the team?
I do what's best for the team.
I want to back my players when they're having a tough time. But the team always comes first. I make the decisions I need to when we're trying to get something out of a game.
He won't always play.
It's a manager's job to make decisions. No player at this club is sure of his place in the team. It's important the lads know that there's always somebody else waiting to put pressure on them.
You have to take your chance when it comes.

I try to make sure every player gets treated the same here. %1s is no different. If you get an opportunity to play, you have to make the most of it. Prove to me you're worth a regular place in the team.
Why did you leave %1s out?
I think everyone knows %1s has been struggling for form recently. People are interested in how you've handled the situation. What was the thinking behind leaving him out today?
Every player has to earn his place.
I have to look at the bigger picture. %1s knows he's not been anything like his best lately. It's the same for every player. If you're not playing well, you can't expect to be in the team.
The team has to come first.
The lad knows this is nothing personal. As manager, I always have to put the best interests of the team first. I rate him as a player but, at the moment, he's not playing well enough to be picked.
I want to see a reaction.
I've got a strong squad of players to pick from. That's good for the club. %1s knows he has to earn the right to a place in the team. I want to see a reaction from him now to being left out.
Were you pleased with %1s's display?

He deserves all the credit.
The lad's on fire at the moment and that's tribute to his hard work as well as his talent. %1s deserves the praise he's getting. I hope he can continue to turn in displays like today's.
He needs to keep his feet on the ground.
Of course he's playing well at the moment. But he needs to make sure the attention doesn't go to his head. We've got a long season in front of us. The key is consistency now.

I was very pleased with what %1s gave us today. I need him performing at that level as often as possible now. That's what sets the best players apart. They're able to sustain performance levels week after week.

Despite the win today %1s didn't hit the form expected of him. What does this mean for his future as a starting player?
Nothing is for granted

Ups and downs

We all have our ups and downs and thankfully the team managed to pick up the slack today. I'm happy to see players in the squad supporting each other, it speaks to the unity of this fantastic group of players.
He can bounce back
I am certain %1s has what it takes to avoid making a habit of bad performances. I'm sure he will bounce back.

Why was %1s left out?
There were a lot of positives to take out of today's game. People are wondering, though, why you decided to leave %1s out of the line-up. Is there a problem?
What a stupid question!
I'm standing here after an excellent performance from my team. I'm ready to talk about how well we played and how pleased I am we won the game. But you want to talk about a player I left out?
The team's always the priority.

I go into every game with the same intention: to win. And I pick the team that I think has the best chance of achieving that. So, l left %1s out because I thought it was the right decision for the team today.
We've got competition for places here.

I've got a strong squad here. The boys were great today and I'm really pleased with the result. Competition for places can only be a good thing at the club. I want every player to be hungry for his chance.
Will you keep backing %1s?
You've trusted %1s to play his way back into form but today was another game that he's been unable to make a difference in. How do you see the situation? Will you still give him chances to play?
It looks like getting %1s another chance hasn't paid off as he couldn't help the team grab a win today. Will you still back him up in the coming weeks?
I'll do what's best for the team.
I don't pick %1s as a favour to the boy. He needs to prove that he deserves to be in the team. I know I've got other players who are ready to come in and take their chance in his position.
We'll keep backing the lad.

I think it's unfair to blame the team's shortcomings on one player. I think %1s is just a bit short on confidence right now. But he'll come back from this. We need to stick together now as a group until he does.
Every player deserves a chance.

I've got a squad of players here, all of them hungry to prove themselves. I won't make a special case for %1s. Like every other lad in that dressing room, he has to prove he's worth a place in the team.
Do you regret not playing %1s?

It wasn't a good day for us and I'm unhappy about the result. There are more important problems to resolve than worrying about what difference %1s might have made, to be honest.
I'll take responsibility for my decisions.
I make decisions before every game based on my judgement of what's best for the team. Maybe I got it wrong today not picking the lad. I'll take full responsibility for that, of course.

We've got a great result and I'm delighted with how the boys played. So why ask me that question? I took him off him off because I decided that was the right thing to do. Simple as that.
